      <p>{`While crowns are very strong, they can still be damaged. If your crown feels loose or you experience any pain, contact your dentist promptly.`}</p>
      <p>{`Crowns today are more accurate and quicker to place thanks to modern tools. Unlike the messy molds and long wait times of the past, we now use CAD/CAM systems that take a 3D scan of your tooth with a small camera. This lets us design the crown on a computer, and often, we can create and place it on the same day.`}</p>
      <p>{`Digital scans are quick and comfortable, replacing the old putty trays. We also use durable, natural-looking materials like zirconia.`}</p>
      <p>{`Crowns are chosen when a tooth needs full coverage for protection and strength. Other restorative options are available depending on the extent of the damage:`}</p>
      <p>{`At AnaBella Family and Cosmetic Dentistry, we will help you compare these options to decide on the best treatment for your needs.`}</p>
